<title type="html"><![CDATA[Is Windows Classic Start Menu Style (as in 3.6.8) Defunct?]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=1593&amp;p=8146#p8146"><![CDATA[
My Windows7 sp1 laptop, using Classic Start Menu 3.6.8, uses Start Menu Style Windows Classic. I like that style VERY much, and am not willing to give it up.<br /><br />But the illustrations at <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.classicshell.net/gallery/">http://www.classicshell.net/gallery/</a><!-- m --> suggest to me that the 3.6.8 Windows Classic Start Menu Style is defunct in version 4.0.2. Is that correct?<br /><br />I would very much appreciate the answer, because I have put a lot of effort into customizing 3.6.8's Classic Start Menu (a main folder column plus two alternative second folder columns; no third folder column), and I don't think I am willing to give it up, despite the 4.0.2's additional technical features (although mostly for Windows 8.x instead of Windows7sp1).<br /><br />A second question is: If I do decide I want to install version 4.0.2, do I first need to uninstall version 3.6.8?<br /><br />Thanks for any relevant information.<br /><br />R.N. (Roger) Folsom<br /><br />________________________________________________________________<br /><br />P.S. Comment: Despite Microsoft's belief that most computers are used by multiple people with different preferences (instead of my case and my wife's case, where we each have our own computers, each with Administrator and Standard User accounts), it sure would be convenient to install Classic Start Menu in All Users.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=487">RNFolsom</a> — Mon Oct 28, 2013 11:11 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
